17/11/2002
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Prime Minister Branko Crvenkovski and his Italian counterpart Silvio Berlusconi signed four bilateral co-operation agreements in Skopje on Friday (15 November). The agreements aim to strengthen co-operation in the fields of tourism, culture, education, science, and cinema production and in a joint project for environmental protection in the Radika River valley. On Friday, Berlusconi met with President Boris Trajkovski, reiterating Italy's support for Macedonian efforts to join NATO and the EU. He added that the Italian parliament would soon ratify the Stabilisation and Association Agreement signed between Macedonia and the EU. (MIA - 16/11/02; MIA, Makfax - 15/11/02)
